description:
Lines 46-50 (users box) and 164-168 (input box) duplicate the focus border styling:

    let border_style = if state.focus == Focus::SomeVariant {
        Style::default().fg(Color::Yellow)
    } else {
        Style::default()
    };

Extract: fn focus_border_style(is_focused: bool) -> Style { ... }

Call from both draw_users and draw_input. Benefits:
- Single source of truth for focus visual design
- Easy to update focus styling everywhere (add Bold, etc.)
- Prevents divergence where one box gets updated and the other doesn't
